people and organisations. This freedom means a person or organisation
has the right to say, or not say, whatever they choose. A natural
extension of the right is the right to influence others to say, or not
say, things on your behalf. This influence may flow from your sparkling
personality, or from your wallet.

Freedom is always a two edged sword. Some people don't seem to
understand the nature of true freedom. With true freedom it is not
possible to compel another to do something on your behalf. That would
mean the other person or organisation did not enjoy freedom.

Freedom of speech. Isn't it great?
